MAN Energy Solutions enables it customers to achieve sustainable value creation in the transition towards a carbon neutral future. Addressing tomorrow's challenges within the marine, energy and industrial sectors, we improve efficiency and performance at a systematic level. Leading the way in advanced engineering for more than 250 years, we provide a unique portfolio of technologies. Headquartered in Germany, MAN Energy Solutions employs some 15,000 people at over 120 sites globally. Our after sales brand, MAN PrimeServ offers a vast network of service centers to our customers all over the world. For our Benelux organization we are currently looking for a Field Service Engineer Turbochargers for our Turbochargers Department in Antwerpen.

Your Tasks:
Being able to carry out maintenance and repair;

What will you do?
Within the Safety & Security team, you will have varied duties as a field/support engineer:
You will perform installations, maintenance and repairs on the high-tech solutions at our customers;
You will install and configure electronic security systems;
Together with our customers, you will examine what optimisations can be made to their existing infrastructure in order to achieve a more secure application;
You will help to look for the possible added value for the customers in terms of security;
You will train our customers on the installed technology;

